---please connect with post gress with docker

this is the command used for running postgress in local host
1)docker run -d -i --name postgres_1 -p 5432:5432 -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD="password" postgres:latest
this is the command to execute postgress
2)docker exec -it postgres_1 bash;  
3)psql -U postgres -- this will connect to postgres
4)\l this will print all the database 
5)\c test -- this will connnect to our db test 
---after word you can create and insert value in db using sql commands

6)\d this will list all the tables in db 

7)ctrl+D to come back to docker
8)docker stop postgres_1

and insert user in it
